\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 The Usecase: Corporate Expense Management\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Processing employee expense reports is a major administrative bottleneck. Managers are flooded with low-value, routine items (like coffee or office supplies) that could easily be automated, while high-value expenses (like flights or hardware) require careful risk reviews and manual authorization.\
In this codelab, you will build an event-driven 
\f1\b ambient expense agent
\f0\b0  that acts as an automated triage queue. It processes incoming expense report submissions (simulated as Pub/Sub messages) and routes them based on the transaction value:\
