\f1\b\fs36 \strokec2 \
What is an ambient agent?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 An 
\f1\b ambient agent
\f0\b0  is an asynchronous, event-driven AI agent that operates in the background without a direct user interface (like a chat window). Instead of waiting for a person to type a prompt, an ambient agent listens for system events or triggers (such as Pub/Sub messages, Cloud Storage file uploads, or database changes), runs its workflow independently, and delivers its results to downstream services or notification channels.\
Right now, your workflow is driven by interactive chat. To make it 
\f1\b ambient
\f0\b0 , we put it behind an ADK 
\f1\b trigger endpoint
\f0\b0  so a Pub/Sub or Eventarc message starts it automatically.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 How ADK Handles Ambient Triggers\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 To expose your workflow to incoming events, you mount your ADK agent within a FastAPI application. Once mounted, ADK automatically provides built-in event endpoints, such as 
\f4\b\fs26 \strokec2 /apps/expense_agent/trigger/pubsub
\f0\b0\fs24 \strokec2 .\
When a Pub/Sub push message arrives at this endpoint, ADK automatically manages the underlying event mechanics for you (see the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://adk.dev/runtime/ambient-agents/"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Ambient Agents guide}}):\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Automatic Decoding:
\f0\b0  It Base64-decodes the incoming Pub/Sub message payload into a normalized JSON structure: \uc0\u8232 \u8232 
\f3\fs26 \{ "data": <decoded expense payload>, "attributes": \{ "source": "..." \} \}\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Session Isolation:
\f0\b0  It creates a dedicated, fresh workflow session for every incoming event.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Session Tracking:
\f0\b0  It automatically assigns the Pub/Sub subscription name as the session's 
\f3\fs26 userId
\f0\fs24 . You will use this ID later to look up and manage paused sessions during local testing.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 To enable this, we will create a FastAPI entry point (
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 expense_agent/fast_api_app.py
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 ) that mounts our ADK workflow and serves these trigger endpoints.\
\uc0\u55357 \u56393  Copy-paste the following prompt to Antigravity:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
