\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Because AI models are probabilistic, agent quality is evaluated qualitatively across the execution trajectory and final outcome (see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://adk.dev/evaluate/"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Why Evaluate Agents}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cloud.google.com/gemini-enterprise-agent-platform/optimize/evaluation/agent-evaluation"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Agent Platform Evaluation Docs}}). We will use 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 agents-cli
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  and the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.skills.sh/google/agents-cli/google-agents-cli-eval"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 google-agents-cli-eval}} skill to run local 
\f1\b LLM-as-judge
\f0\b0  evaluations.\
